      'Placeholder — list the open-source work here. Libraries you have published, contributions to projects you use, tools you have built for the community. A GitHub profile link works well here as a starting point.',
      'What is worth highlighting? Contributions that were merged into major projects. Libraries with real downloads or users. Tools that solve a problem you could not find an existing solution for. Documentation improvements if they significantly improved a project you rely on.',
      'Open source contributions signal how you work in public, how you communicate technical decisions, and whether you engage with communities beyond your own work. Update this with your actual contributions and replace the placeholder GitHub handle.',
    ],
